org.hl7.vmr.r2

Class CompositeSubstanceProposal

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hl7.vmr.r2.ClinicalStatement
      • org.hl7.vmr.r2.SubstanceClinicalStatementBase
        • org.hl7.vmr.r2.SubstanceAdministrationProposal
          • org.hl7.vmr.r2.CompositeSubstanceProposal

  • public class CompositeSubstanceProposal
extends SubstanceAdministrationProposal
    A class representing a proposal for a composite medication such as IV fluid that may consist of one or more additives mixed into a diluent. Additives and diluents are represented as constituents with the appropriate constituentType.

    Java class for CompositeSubstanceProposal complex type.

    The following schema fragment specifies the expected content contained within this class. 

     <complexType name="CompositeSubstanceProposal">
   <complexContent>
     <extension base="{urn:hl7-org:vmr:r2}SubstanceAdministrationProposal">
       <sequence>
         <element name="constituent" type="{urn:hl7-org:vmr:r2}Constituent" maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="totalVolume" type="{urn:hl7-org:cdsdt:r2}IVL_PQ" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="pH" type="{urn:hl7-org:cdsdt:r2}INT" minOccurs="0"/>
       </sequence>
     </extension>
   </complexContent>
 </complexType>

    • Method Detail

      • getConstituent

        public List<Constituent> getConstituent()
        Gets the value of the constituent property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the constituent property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getConstituent().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list Constituent
